WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.068 --> 00:00:02.469
[Faith] <i>Previously on</i>
Will Trent

2
00:00:02.604 --> 00:00:04.471
-[Malcolm] <i>I love you.</i>
-[Faith] <i>I love you too.</i>

3
00:00:04.606 --> 00:00:06.774
You know there's only one way
this ends. Faith.

4
00:00:06.908 --> 00:00:09.009
With him in prison.

5
00:00:09.142 --> 00:00:10.545
And where does that leave me?

6
00:00:10.678 --> 00:00:14.916
And if we could go back.
I would introduce myself
as Faith.

7
00:00:15.048 --> 00:00:17.619
But we'd still end up
right here.

8
00:00:17.752 --> 00:00:19.521
Because you rob banks.

9
00:00:19.654 --> 00:00:21.890
And I arrest people
who rob banks.

10
00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:23.758
I looked into the worms.

11
00:00:23.892 --> 00:00:26.426
Fascinating thing is
they can grow up to 30 feet
inside human intestines.

12
00:00:26.561 --> 00:00:27.896
They have six rows of teeth.

13
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:30.464
Th-They can live inside you
for years without any symptoms.

14
00:00:30.598 --> 00:00:31.733
I don't think we've met.

15
00:00:31.866 --> 00:00:33.668
-Will.
-Oh. you're Will.

16
00:00:33.801 --> 00:00:34.936
-Nice to meet you.
-Hi.

17
00:00:35.068 --> 00:00:37.304
This is your family.
I'm your family.

18
00:00:37.437 --> 00:00:38.673
It's not just you
heading into danger.

19
00:00:38.806 --> 00:00:40.240
You trust me
to take care of her?

20
00:00:40.374 --> 00:00:42.644
That's what
this stage of love is. I guess.

21
00:00:44.913 --> 00:00:46.714
[person 1] I'm stupid.

22
00:00:46.848 --> 00:00:48.248
[person 2] No. you're drunk.

23
00:00:48.382 --> 00:00:51.218
Step. Again. [grunts]

24
00:00:51.351 --> 00:00:53.120
[person 1] Do you think
he'll text?

25
00:00:53.253 --> 00:00:54.254
[person 2] Nope.

26
00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:55.757
I thought he was the one.

27
00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:59.861
[person 2] After three drinks
and 15 seconds of OTP?

28
00:00:59.994 --> 00:01:02.229
-[groans]
-Girl. I told you

29
00:01:02.362 --> 00:01:04.431
-[glass bottle clinks]
-[distant laughter]

30
00:01:06.501 --> 00:01:07.535
[person 2] Hello?

31
00:01:09.269 --> 00:01:12.072
-[groaning] I think
I'm gonna puke.
-Ugh.

32
00:01:12.205 --> 00:01:15.075
Not in my dress. It's vintage.

33
00:01:16.176 --> 00:01:18.680
-Here. don't fall in.
-[groans]

34
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

35
00:01:28.957 --> 00:01:29.991
[gasps]

36
00:01:31.859 --> 00:01:34.629
[screaming]

37
00:01:37.097 --> 00:01:39.867
So. all babies are cute. right?
Just not this one.

38
00:01:40.001 --> 00:01:42.637
No. they are not all cute.
but ours will be
because she's ours.

39
00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:43.972
She's gonna be cute.

40
00:01:44.104 --> 00:01:46.473
CPR week is gonna be so easy
for a cop and a doctor.

41
00:01:46.608 --> 00:01:48.108
-[sighing] Oh. I hope so.
-I hope so.

42
00:01:48.241 --> 00:01:50.143
Last week's swaddling
was harder than med school.

43
00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:53.180
-[Angie] Uh. we got this.
-[Seth laughing]

44
00:01:53.313 --> 00:01:55.016
Does your baby's safety
amuse you?

45
00:01:55.148 --> 00:01:57.184
-Uh. no. we were just. um--
-[teacher] Hey. y'all.

46
00:01:58.151 --> 00:02:00.788
I'm Ingrid.
I'll be teacher this week.

47
00:02:00.922 --> 00:02:06.126
In 2023. 6.4% of newborns
died in accidents.

48
00:02:06.961 --> 00:02:09.564
Let's keep your baby alive.
shall we?

49
00:02:09.697 --> 00:02:11.198
[♪ mid-tempo
jazz music playing]

50
00:02:11.331 --> 00:02:14.836
-8. 9. 10. 11. 12. 13. 14
-9. 10. 11. 12. 13 Yep.

51
00:02:14.969 --> 00:02:17.672
-So. your baby can breathe.
-Yay!

52
00:02:17.805 --> 00:02:19.774
-But what about the fire?
-What fire?

53
00:02:19.907 --> 00:02:21.174
A fire has started!

54
00:02:21.308 --> 00:02:23.011
Where is
the closest extinguisher?

55
00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:24.277
-Is there one in every room?
-Oh.

56
00:02:24.411 --> 00:02:25.913
What is your evacuation plan?

57
00:02:26.047 --> 00:02:28.148
Too late. baby's dead.

58
00:02:28.281 --> 00:02:29.517
Try again?

59
00:02:31.052 --> 00:02:32.954
-You guys big readers?
-[both] Yeah.

60
00:02:33.087 --> 00:02:34.522
Are your bookshelves secure?

61
00:02:35.823 --> 00:02:37.625
Crushed! Baby's dead.

62
00:02:37.759 --> 00:02:38.826
Again.

63
00:02:39.661 --> 00:02:42.195
-Blinds on your windows?
-Yeah.

64
00:02:42.329 --> 00:02:44.632
Don't want that sun
to wake the baby.

65
00:02:44.766 --> 00:02:45.867
Strangled!

66
00:02:47.234 --> 00:02:48.636
-Baby's dead. We got it.
-Baby's dead.

67
00:02:56.110 --> 00:02:57.477
[baby doll cries]

68
00:02:59.279 --> 00:03:01.883
[Will] Did you know the victim.
Paxton Cole?

69
00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:03.751
Yes. very well. [sighs]

70
00:03:03.885 --> 00:03:06.154
Paxton Cole was
a leader on campus.

71
00:03:06.286 --> 00:03:09.423
Honor roll.
president of his fraternity.

72
00:03:10.825 --> 00:03:12.225
What fraternity is that?

73
00:03:12.359 --> 00:03:13.761
Delta Chi Kappa.

74
00:03:14.595 --> 00:03:17.965
-He was a boy
with a very bright future.
-[knocking on door]

75
00:03:18.099 --> 00:03:21.969
Chancellor B.
the Boozy Booster brunch
is starting in ten minutes.

76
00:03:22.103 --> 00:03:24.337
Sheila. I'm very aware
of the time. thank you.

77
00:03:25.173 --> 00:03:26.507
[Sheila] Mm-hmm.

78
00:03:26.641 --> 00:03:30.310
I'm sorry. am I keeping you
from your Boozy Booster brunch?

79
00:03:31.179 --> 00:03:32.914
[chuckling] My apologies.

80
00:03:33.047 --> 00:03:34.716
There's a lot going on. [sighs]

81
00:03:34.849 --> 00:03:36.017
It's homecoming week.

82
00:03:36.150 --> 00:03:37.552
Alumni are already arriving.

83
00:03:37.685 --> 00:03:39.721
Such a terrible time
for something like this.

84
00:03:39.854 --> 00:03:45.026
Yeah. you know.
such an inconvenience.
but this young man is dead.

85
00:03:45.159 --> 00:03:46.761
[sighs] I sound callous.
forgive me.

86
00:03:46.894 --> 00:03:49.764
It's just that
this is the university's
biggest fundraising period.

87
00:03:49.897 --> 00:03:50.932
I'm sure you understand.

88
00:03:52.867 --> 00:03:54.769
Where'd you go to school.
Special Agent?

89
00:03:56.436 --> 00:03:58.438
I earned my degree online.

90
00:03:59.040 --> 00:04:00.074
Oh.

91
00:04:01.341 --> 00:04:04.277
Well. that's the great thing
about America. isn't it?

92
00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:06.848
Education for all.
no matter how humble.

93
00:04:09.016 --> 00:04:10.885
How was Paxton as a student?

94
00:04:11.786 --> 00:04:15.089
Did he ever get into trouble.
any conflicts with classmates?

95
00:04:15.223 --> 00:04:17.992
You can't think Paxton
was targeted deliberately.

96
00:04:18.126 --> 00:04:20.895
That courtyard
where he was found.
that's city property.

97
00:04:21.028 --> 00:04:23.430
He was either mugged
or he interrupted a drug deal.

98
00:04:23.564 --> 00:04:24.632
This is about Atlanta.

99
00:04:24.766 --> 00:04:27.869
Paxton Cole was stripped
to his underwear

100
00:04:28.401 --> 00:04:30.872
and left in front of
the university like a dead rat.

101
00:04:31.506 --> 00:04:34.575
duct tape over his mouth
with words written across it.

102
00:04:35.243 --> 00:04:37.678
Whoever killed him
is making a statement.

103
00:04:37.812 --> 00:04:40.081
This isn't about
stealing a wallet.

104
00:04:42.717 --> 00:04:44.317
[knocking on door]

105
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:47.655
Sir. the Wine and Winners
dinner party sent back
your rough draft.

106
00:04:47.789 --> 00:04:49.824
They made a lot of changes.

107
00:04:49.957 --> 00:04:51.125
Thank you. Sheila.

108
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:55.563
Special Agent Trent.
this situation is tragic.

109
00:04:55.696 --> 00:04:59.332
I'd like to
see the matter wrapped up
as quickly as possible. [sighs]

110
00:04:59.801 --> 00:05:00.935
Do you need any help?

111
00:05:02.236 --> 00:05:03.571
Any other resources?

112
00:05:04.739 --> 00:05:06.473
I'll do my humble best.

113
00:05:15.583 --> 00:05:17.985
See. that's the problem
with Generation Z.
They're lazy.

114
00:05:18.119 --> 00:05:20.822
Always talking about.
"Protect my peace."
Can't even pedal a bicycle.

115
00:05:20.955 --> 00:05:24.025
-You know. back in my day--
-You sound like
you are 10.000 years old.

116
00:05:24.158 --> 00:05:25.693
If you don't
let these kids live

117
00:05:26.426 --> 00:05:27.895
Delta Chi Kappa
is just right up here.

118
00:05:28.029 --> 00:05:29.630
[Angie] Wait up. assholes.
I'm pregnant.

119
00:05:30.264 --> 00:05:32.700
-Hey.
-[Michael] How'd you find us?

120
00:05:32.834 --> 00:05:34.635
[pants] I used Find My Friend
to track Faith.

121
00:05:34.769 --> 00:05:35.837
-Hi. friend.
-Hi.

122
00:05:35.970 --> 00:05:38.039
-Wait. you guys
track each other?
-Yeah.

123
00:05:38.172 --> 00:05:39.707
I'm your partner.
You should track me.

124
00:05:39.841 --> 00:05:41.341
How was the parenting class?

125
00:05:41.474 --> 00:05:43.578
Terrible.
I killed my baby in more ways

126
00:05:43.711 --> 00:05:45.112
-than I thought was possible.
-Oh.

127
00:05:45.246 --> 00:05:47.380
[Angie] This place is so fancy.
80K a year?

128
00:05:47.515 --> 00:05:48.850
Yeah. a total rip-off.

129
00:05:48.983 --> 00:05:51.052
I never even finished college.
I'm doing great.

130
00:05:51.185 --> 00:05:52.452
Yeah. you're 38
with a roommate.

131
00:05:52.587 --> 00:05:54.889
-Hey.
-Okay. careful.

132
00:05:55.022 --> 00:05:57.525
[♪ rap music playing faintly]

133
00:06:06.167 --> 00:06:10.171
APD. We need to talk to you
about your frat brother.
Paxton Cole.

134
00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:16.310
I did say that out loud. right?

135
00:06:16.443 --> 00:06:17.511
-You did.
-Okay.

136
00:06:18.179 --> 00:06:19.714
-That's sketch.
-Mmm. yep.

137
00:06:21.148 --> 00:06:23.383
APD. we asked you a question.

138
00:06:24.352 --> 00:06:25.620
Paxton's not here right now.

139
00:06:25.753 --> 00:06:28.421
Hey! Pledges don't speak.

140
00:06:29.257 --> 00:06:30.958
Clean out your mouth now.

141
00:06:32.293 --> 00:06:34.427
-[pledge gags]
-Hey. hey. hey!
We was talking to him.

142
00:06:34.562 --> 00:06:37.164
The rest of you.
think about it.

143
00:06:41.068 --> 00:06:44.672
Listen. I'll haul all of you
into the station
if somebody doesn't answer.

144
00:06:44.805 --> 00:06:47.608
Your frat brother
Paxton Cole is dead.

145
00:06:49.442 --> 00:06:52.680
So I need everyone to speak.
or I'll arrest you for hazing.

146
00:06:52.813 --> 00:06:54.481
which is illegal
in the state of Georgia.

147
00:06:54.615 --> 00:06:56.717
Wait. the body they found.
that was Paxton?

148
00:06:56.851 --> 00:07:00.121
-You. what's your name?
-Sean. but the guys
call me Legacy.

149
00:07:00.788 --> 00:07:02.422
[♪ "Bet On Me" playing]

150
00:07:02.556 --> 00:07:04.392
♪ <i>Everyday that I wake up</i> ♪

151
00:07:04.525 --> 00:07:07.194
♪ <i>Everything make me taller</i>
<i>Everything that I go through</i> ♪

152
00:07:07.328 --> 00:07:10.564
♪ <i>Everything make me smarter</i>
<i>Everything that I go through</i> ♪

153
00:07:10.698 --> 00:07:12.566
♪ <i>Everything get me charged</i>
<i>Ooh. yeah</i> ♪

154
00:07:12.700 --> 00:07:13.968
♪ <i>Heavy stepper</i> ♪

155
00:07:14.101 --> 00:07:15.468
♪ <i>Lie to yourself</i>
<i>Don't lie to me</i> ♪

156
00:07:15.603 --> 00:07:17.138
♪ <i>'Cause I won't let you</i> ♪

157
00:07:17.271 --> 00:07:18.706
♪ <i>I bring out the best</i>
<i>If it ain't you</i> ♪

158
00:07:18.839 --> 00:07:20.241
♪ <i>Then I can't help you</i> ♪

159
00:07:21.542 --> 00:07:22.777
It's not my fault.

160
00:07:27.515 --> 00:07:31.252
So. Griffin.
your nickname is Badger.

161
00:07:31.953 --> 00:07:33.154
That's interesting.

162
00:07:33.888 --> 00:07:37.191
You know. badgers can be
quite aggressive
when threatened.

163
00:07:37.959 --> 00:07:39.560
Did you ever feel threatened
by Paxton?

164
00:07:39.694 --> 00:07:41.195
I swear I didn't hurt him.

165
00:07:41.329 --> 00:07:43.764
Hmm.
So why were you avoiding us
like an ex you cheated on?

166
00:07:43.898 --> 00:07:45.132
I was afraid my

167
00:07:46.133 --> 00:07:47.467
business might be implicated.

168
00:07:47.601 --> 00:07:49.469
