-We'll see.

175
00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:10.658
I want to know about Paxton.

176
00:08:10.791 --> 00:08:12.660
Was he a part of
your little economic venture?

177
00:08:12.793 --> 00:08:15.963
No. ma'am.
But last night at the party.
we were running low on beer.

178
00:08:16.097 --> 00:08:18.165
-so he and Sharkey
said they'd--
-Sharkey

179
00:08:18.299 --> 00:08:19.967
I need real. full names.

180
00:08:20.101 --> 00:08:24.038
Oh. Greg Sharkens.
he's another DK.
They went to pick up some kegs.

181
00:08:24.171 --> 00:08:25.272
Using fake IDs.

182
00:08:25.406 --> 00:08:27.541
Yeah. that was the last time
I saw them.

183
00:08:27.675 --> 00:08:28.709
Both of them?

184
00:08:29.176 --> 00:08:31.145
-You know where?
-To get beer.
I don't know where.

185
00:08:31.278 --> 00:08:32.813
Was there any beef
between the two of them?

186
00:08:33.347 --> 00:08:36.250
-I mean. no.
not that I know of.
-Huh.

187
00:08:37.218 --> 00:08:39.720
-Can I go?
-No. Badger.

188
00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:41.389
Federal crime. remember?

189
00:08:42.990 --> 00:08:45.693
Do you have any idea
where your brother Sharkey is?

190
00:08:45.826 --> 00:08:47.461
No. sir. Haven't seen him. sir.

191
00:08:47.595 --> 00:08:49.163
I don't know
where they went for beer.

192
00:08:49.296 --> 00:08:51.899
We can't always go to
the same liquor store because

193
00:08:52.033 --> 00:08:53.734
Fake IDs. We know.

194
00:08:53.868 --> 00:08:55.002
Sharkey?

195
00:08:55.136 --> 00:08:56.404
Nah. I haven't seen him.

196
00:08:56.537 --> 00:08:57.571
Not for a bit.

197
00:08:57.705 --> 00:08:59.407
You ever see Paxton
and Sharkey argue?

198
00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:00.875
Fight over a girl?

199
00:09:01.409 --> 00:09:04.678
Those two. they were day ones.
Besties. sir.

200
00:09:04.812 --> 00:09:05.813
Sharkey?

201
00:09:06.647 --> 00:09:08.349
No. he'd never hurt Doorbell.

202
00:09:08.482 --> 00:09:10.885
Doorbell? You mean Paxton?

203
00:09:11.018 --> 00:09:13.354
-That's what
everyone called him.
-Why?

204
00:09:15.389 --> 00:09:16.791
Get outta here.

205
00:09:17.625 --> 00:09:19.260
[Franklin] Go. Get out.

206
00:09:20.394 --> 00:09:21.796
No one has heard
from Sharkey today.

207
00:09:21.929 --> 00:09:25.232
Everyone says they were tight.
no bad blood.

208
00:09:25.366 --> 00:09:28.402
The victim went by "Doorbell."
That's all we've got.

209
00:09:28.537 --> 00:09:32.673
That's the yield of
three trained detectives.

210
00:09:32.807 --> 00:09:35.443
Maybe we get them
off their home turf.
make 'em squirm?

211
00:09:36.210 --> 00:09:37.278
I got something better.

212
00:09:37.845 --> 00:09:39.613
-The belly.
-[Faith chuckles]

213
00:09:39.747 --> 00:09:43.717
The Lasso of Truth. [sighs]

214
00:09:43.851 --> 00:09:44.819
Go ahead. mama.

215
00:09:44.952 --> 00:09:47.455
[chuckles. groans]

216
00:09:47.955 --> 00:09:49.023
[sighs]

217
00:09:49.156 --> 00:09:51.192
Oh. my God. Oh. wait.

218
00:09:51.325 --> 00:09:52.927
Ma'am. hold on. Are you

219
00:09:53.060 --> 00:09:54.161
Should I call somebody?

220
00:09:54.295 --> 00:09:55.396
Oh. no.

221
00:09:55.530 --> 00:09:57.098
I still got
a ways to go. I just

222
00:09:57.231 --> 00:09:59.600
Sometimes I gotta stretch.
you know. [pants]

223
00:09:59.733 --> 00:10:02.169
Her head is
up against my lungs.
It makes it hard to breathe.

224
00:10:02.303 --> 00:10:04.105
[stammering] Well.
do you need a chair?

225
00:10:04.238 --> 00:10:06.907
[sighs] Oh.
that would be great.
actually. Sean.

226
00:10:08.109 --> 00:10:09.143
Thank you.

227
00:10:09.944 --> 00:10:11.979
-[sighs]
-[Sean] Is this your first?

228
00:10:12.113 --> 00:10:14.715
-Yeah. Yeah. it is.
-Wow.

229
00:10:14.849 --> 00:10:17.017
-Well. you must
have chill parents.
-[sighs]

230
00:10:17.151 --> 00:10:19.920
My dad wants me engaged
before I graduate.
married next year.

231
00:10:20.054 --> 00:10:21.889
with a kid on the way
the year after that.

232
00:10:22.356 --> 00:10:24.959
-That's a lot of pressure.
-[sighing] Yeah.

233
00:10:25.092 --> 00:10:26.994
I guess that's why
they call you Legacy. though.

234
00:10:27.128 --> 00:10:28.395
Fifth generation.

235
00:10:28.530 --> 00:10:29.630
Wow.

236
00:10:29.763 --> 00:10:31.198
You're missing last year.

237
00:10:33.502 --> 00:10:34.536
Yeah. a pledge broke it.

238
00:10:35.703 --> 00:10:37.671
