00:22:59.981 --> 00:23:01.048
And he was at the Gatsby party?

487
00:23:01.182 --> 00:23:03.751
-Yeah. he was a DK pledge.
-Name?

488
00:23:03.885 --> 00:23:05.418
Need a name.

489
00:23:08.589 --> 00:23:10.224
[mouthing] One second.

490
00:23:10.358 --> 00:23:13.361
Of course. Mrs. Guggenheim.
whatever you need.

491
00:23:13.493 --> 00:23:15.696
I'm seated with
the GBI right now.

492
00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:18.566
He assures me
an arrest is imminent.

493
00:23:18.699 --> 00:23:20.768
[chuckles] Okay.

494
00:23:20.902 --> 00:23:23.470
Call anytime. Goodbye.

495
00:23:25.106 --> 00:23:26.374
[sighs]

496
00:23:26.507 --> 00:23:28.910
-A lot of concerned parents
out there.
-Mmm.

497
00:23:29.543 --> 00:23:30.912
You being one of them.

498
00:23:31.545 --> 00:23:33.748
Your son Sean's a DK.
as were you.

499
00:23:33.881 --> 00:23:35.349
It all makes sense.

500
00:23:35.983 --> 00:23:38.986
You tried to protect him.
tried to protect
the fraternity.

501
00:23:39.120 --> 00:23:41.488
but all you've really done is
paint targets on their backs.

502
00:23:41.622 --> 00:23:44.325
I have no idea
what you're talking about.
Detective.

503
00:23:44.457 --> 00:23:45.893
-Are you
-Special Agent.

504
00:23:46.027 --> 00:23:49.363
What I'm talking about
is DK's spotless record.

505
00:23:49.496 --> 00:23:51.799
That's you
cleaning up their mess.

506
00:23:51.933 --> 00:23:53.433
shielding them
from any accountability.

507
00:23:53.567 --> 00:23:55.503
That is a gross
misrepresentation.

508
00:23:56.404 --> 00:23:57.605
These are good boys.

509
00:23:58.406 --> 00:24:01.108
School gives them
and every student

510
00:24:01.242 --> 00:24:03.044
an environment for them
to learn and grow.

511
00:24:03.177 --> 00:24:05.413
not be scrutinized
for the slightest misstep.

512
00:24:05.546 --> 00:24:08.115
Chancellor.
I believe one of these missteps

513
00:24:08.249 --> 00:24:11.419
is the reason Paxton Cole
and Greg Sharkens are dead.

514
00:24:11.552 --> 00:24:15.455
More DKs may be in danger.
including your son.

515
00:24:15.589 --> 00:24:18.960
I need to know
what motivated these attacks.

516
00:24:19.093 --> 00:24:20.328
Motivated?

517
00:24:21.362 --> 00:24:24.065
I do not pretend
to know your job.
Special Agent.

518
00:24:24.565 --> 00:24:27.301
but I cannot see
how victim blaming
is the best course

519
00:24:27.435 --> 00:24:29.303
for keeping these kids safe.

520
00:24:29.437 --> 00:24:31.372
-and that is my priority.
-[phone chimes]

521
00:24:31.505 --> 00:24:32.807
[Eduardo] <i>Angie is calling.</i>

522
00:24:33.441 --> 00:24:35.910
-[phone chimes]
<i>-Angie is calling.</i>

523
00:24:38.446 --> 00:24:41.382
Ask the chancellor
about Barry Evers.

524
00:24:44.018 --> 00:24:45.853
Tell me about Barry Evers.

525
00:24:47.989 --> 00:24:49.256
Barry Evers. Yes.

526
00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:50.825
[sighs] Terrible.

527
00:24:50.958 --> 00:24:52.860
Young man was overwhelmed.

528
00:24:53.327 --> 00:24:55.663
Unable to cope with the rigors
of an elite university.

529
00:24:55.796 --> 00:24:58.366
Got intoxicated
one frigid night.
got lost in the woods.

530
00:24:58.498 --> 00:25:00.568
and died from the elements.

531
00:25:01.535 --> 00:25:02.737
Tragic accident.

532
00:25:02.870 --> 00:25:06.040
Chancellor says Barry's death
was a tragic accident.

533
00:25:06.173 --> 00:25:08.676
-Agent.
who are you speaking with?
-One sec.

534
00:25:08.809 --> 00:25:11.579
-What? No.
-Barry's death was way sus.

535
00:25:11.712 --> 00:25:13.581
[student] <i>No one goes wandering</i>
<i>around the woods late at night</i>

536
00:25:13.714 --> 00:25:15.216
-for no reason.
-Yeah.

537
00:25:15.349 --> 00:25:17.918
[Faith]
There is extremely limited
media coverage of the death

538
00:25:18.052 --> 00:25:20.921
and no mention of him
being a DK pledge.

539
00:25:21.055 --> 00:25:25.793
My sources say
Barry's death was way sus.

540
00:25:27.128 --> 00:25:28.496
"Way sus"?

541
00:25:29.630 --> 00:25:31.766
[scoffs] Where are you getting
this information?

542
00:25:31.899 --> 00:25:33.501
You know. he was a DK pledge.

543
00:25:33.634 --> 00:25:37.705
yet somehow
the fraternity's name
is out of the press entirely.

544
00:25:37.838 --> 00:25:39.907
-[phone ringing]
-Was there an autopsy?

545
00:25:40.041 --> 00:25:41.308
I don't recall.

546
00:25:41.442 --> 00:25:43.344
-Did the family
request an inquiry?
-If they had

547
00:25:43.477 --> 00:25:44.678
Did you talk 'em out of it?

548
00:25:44.812 --> 00:25:46.380
Damn it.
your students are dying!

549
00:25:46.515 --> 00:25:48.015
It was a terrible accident!

550
00:25:48.149 --> 00:25:49.784
It has no relevance here!

551
00:25:52.219 --> 00:25:55.389
Bixby says
Barry has nothing to do
with these deaths.

552
00:25:55.524 --> 00:25:56.657
What do you think?

553
00:25:56.791 --> 00:25:58.426
I think we need to ask Barry.

554
00:25:58.559 --> 00:25:59.627
[gasps]

555
00:26:00.261 --> 00:26:03.464
-Like a séance?
-[Will] <i>Close</i> .

556
00:26:04.198 --> 00:26:05.599
We're gonna exhume his body.

557
00:26:09.538 --> 00:26:11.205
-[grunting]
-[knocking on door]

558
00:26:11.338 --> 00:26:12.273
Come in.

559
00:26:12.406 --> 00:26:14.041
Hey. Will. Oh. hey. uh--

560
00:26:14.175 --> 00:26:16.110
Hey. do me a favor
and brace your core.

561
00:26:16.243 --> 00:26:19.980
I see so many herniated discs
from battles lost
to IKEA's LAGKAPTEN.

562
00:26:20.114 --> 00:26:21.482
Oh.

563
00:26:21.615 --> 00:26:23.784
-Okay. Hello.
-Yeah.

564
00:26:23.918 --> 00:26:26.287
Angie. I think. is down at APD.

565
00:26:26.420 --> 00:26:29.490
No. I just saw her.
We just had lunch.
Um. I actually

566
00:26:29.623 --> 00:26:30.891
I came up to see you.

567
00:26:31.025 --> 00:26:33.627
-Can I give you
a hand with that?
-[grunts]

568
00:26:34.261 --> 00:26:35.396
[exhales]

569
00:26:36.397 --> 00:26:38.199
You know. if you don't mind.
I lost my cuff link.

570
00:26:38.332 --> 00:26:39.934
-It's gotta be in here
somewhere. So
-Sure.

571
00:26:40.601 --> 00:26:42.136
-Yeah. Yeah.
-You just wanna go out?

572
00:26:42.269 --> 00:26:43.637
-Here we go.
-One. two. three. go.

573
00:26:43.771 --> 00:26:45.239
[both straining]

574
00:26:45.372 --> 00:26:47.241
So. uh. you wanted to see me?

575
00:26:47.374 --> 00:26:49.110
Right. yeah. Um. there's this

576
00:26:49.243 --> 00:26:50.978
There's this guest lecture
coming up at GAU.

577
00:26:51.112 --> 00:26:53.147
It's all about human parasites.

578
00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:54.748
I thought
you might be interested.

579
00:26:56.717 --> 00:26:59.753
Why. yes. You know. I
I would find that interesting.
Um

580
00:27:01.956 --> 00:27:03.090
[exhales]

581
00:27:03.624 --> 00:27:05.860
-I don't see it back there.
-No. not this side either.

582
00:27:06.327 --> 00:27:07.361
Okay. let's go back.

583
00:27:07.495 --> 00:27:08.496
-Yep.
-Yep.

584
00:27:09.096 --> 00:27:11.632
You know. Angie and I
went to this baby class.

585
00:27:11.765 --> 00:27:13.000
I don't know if she told you.

586
00:27:13.134 --> 00:27:14.802
Uh. but it kind of
freaked me out.

587
00:27:14.935 --> 00:27:18.540
Made me wanna really shore up
the village around this kid.
you know?

588
00:27:19.473 --> 00:27:20.941
Sure. Hmm.

589
00:27:22.309 --> 00:27:23.811
My family.
they're all up north.

590
00:27:23.944 --> 00:27:26.313
and Angie's family is.
you know. you.

591
00:27:26.447 --> 00:27:29.350
So. I thought
it might be good if we. um

592
00:27:29.483 --> 00:27:30.918
if we became friends.

593
00:27:33.154 --> 00:27:35.656
Aren't we sort of
already friends?

594
00:27:35.789 --> 00:27:39.160
Yeah. I guess
in a non-friends friends
kind of way.

595
00:27:39.293 --> 00:27:40.661
-[knocking on door]
-[Pete] Will?

596
00:27:41.996 --> 00:27:44.131
-Oh. Hey. Seth.
-Hey.

597
00:27:44.932 --> 00:27:48.068
-What are you guys doing?
-We're looking for
Will's cuff link.

598
00:27:48.202 --> 00:27:49.837
You finish
the exhumation autopsy?

599
00:27:49.970 --> 00:27:51.338
Oh. yeah.
I got it ready for you.

600
00:27:51.839 --> 00:27:55.209
Oh. hey.
Look at this. I found it.

601
00:27:55.943 --> 00:27:57.444
Did you say exhumation?

602
00:27:58.479 --> 00:27:59.780
-Thank you.
-Mm-hmm.

603
00:28:01.749 --> 00:28:02.983
You got a few minutes?

604
00:28:05.986 --> 00:28:08.088
Well. it's gooier
than I was expecting.

605
00:28:08.222 --> 00:28:09.390
I envisioned <i>The Mummy.</i>

606
00:28:09.524 --> 00:28:11.392
-That's a great movie.
-Very underrated.

607
00:28:11.526 --> 00:28:13.360
I think the sequel is superior.

608
00:28:15.930 --> 00:28:18.600
Darkened tissue that persists
after a year of decomposition.

609
00:28:18.732 --> 00:28:20.367
Thoughts. gentlemen?

610
00:28:21.035 --> 00:28:22.436
All right. Pete.

611
00:28:22.571 --> 00:28:24.371
-Frostbite?
-[Pete] Correct.

612
00:28:25.206 --> 00:28:26.575
Finding two:

613
00:28:26.707 --> 00:28:28.809
Small hemorrhages
in the stomach
and pancreatic lining

614
00:28:28.943 --> 00:28:31.513
-known as Wischnewski spots.
-Hypothermia. right?

615
00:28:31.646 --> 00:28:34.081
One point to Dr. Seth.
though you had the edge there.

616
00:28:34.215 --> 00:28:35.349
Whoa. are there points?

617
00:28:35.482 --> 00:28:38.219
Not a competition.
but it is also a tie.

618
00:28:39.186 --> 00:28:41.789
Moving along. Splinters found
embedded in his feet

619
00:28:41.922 --> 00:28:44.358
from hickory. black locust.
and cedar trees.

620
00:28:44.491 --> 00:28:47.828
Sounds like he was walking
barefoot in the forest.
That's another point. right?

621
00:28:47.962 --> 00:28:51.198
Yet the responding officers
noted he was found
fully dressed.

622
00:28:51.332 --> 00:28:53.934
Huh.
Speaking of clothing. Pete.
what was the victim buried in?

623
00:28:54.068 --> 00:28:56.504
Oh. suit's there.
I haven't examined it yet.

624
00:28:57.037 --> 00:28:59.273
-Ready for the next finding?
-Yeah. bring it on.

625
00:28:59.406 --> 00:29:02.009
Trace amounts of adhesive
found in the tissue lining

626
00:29:02.142 --> 00:29:04.378
of his inner lips.
teeth and tip of his tongue.

627
00:29:04.512 --> 00:29:06.247
-His mouth was taped shut?
-Yep.

628
00:29:06.380 --> 00:29:10.050
And lastly. gold flakes
found in his stomach.

629
00:29:10.184 --> 00:29:11.218
Goldenkränz.

630
00:29:11.352 --> 00:29:12.786
-Correct. [chuckling]
-Hey.

631
00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:15.256
Hey. Dr. Seth is really
running away with this. Will.

632
00:29:15.389 --> 00:29:16.890
I'm sorry.

633
00:29:17.024 --> 00:29:19.527
This young man was murdered.
I'm not engaging
in a competition.

634
00:29:20.160 --> 00:29:21.495
Because you're losing.

635
00:29:21.630 --> 00:29:22.664
That's correct.

636
00:29:22.796 --> 00:29:24.666
Well. whatever happened
to this poor kid.

637
00:29:24.798 --> 00:29:27.401
the official story
does not match
the evidence on the body.

638
00:29:27.535 --> 00:29:29.303
Because Barry probably
died in his underwear

639
00:29:29.436 --> 00:29:31.305
just like
our present-day victims.

640
00:29:31.438 --> 00:29:34.709
Someone later dressed him.
left him to be found.

641
00:29:34.842 --> 00:29:36.810
Whoever killed Paxton
and Sharkey.

642
00:29:36.944 --> 00:29:38.946
they know the truth
about Barry's death.

643
00:29:41.048 --> 00:29:42.850
Maybe even helped cover it up.

644
00:29:47.254 --> 00:29:50.057
This is a note that Will found
in Barry's burial suit.

645
00:29:50.190 --> 00:29:52.192
presumably tucked in
by someone at the funeral.

646
00:29:52.326 --> 00:29:54.161
"I will never forget."

647
00:29:54.295 --> 00:29:59.099
And this is a photo that Angie
took of Brit's handwriting.

648
00:29:59.233 --> 00:30:00.934
Words on the duct tape
were all caps.

649
00:30:01.068 --> 00:30:03.672
so we couldn't
match them conclusively.

650
00:30:03.804 --> 00:30:05.806
But these two samples.
they match.

651
00:30:05.939 --> 00:30:08.510
I was able to track down
the filing of Brit's NDA.

652
00:30:08.643 --> 00:30:11.312
and I'm still trying to get
access to specific details.

653
00:30:11.445 --> 00:30:14.783
but it was filed
the day after Barry's death.

654
00:30:14.915 --> 00:30:17.284
So the damn NDA
was never about the sex tape.

655
00:30:17.418 --> 00:30:18.352
It was about Barry.

656
00:30:18.485 --> 00:30:20.154
I've been doing this a while.

657
00:30:20.287 --> 00:30:22.590
A million bucks says
the sex tape was a diversion.

658
00:30:22.724 --> 00:30:25.660
Barry dies.
they leak the sex tape.

659
00:30:25.794 --> 00:30:27.895
Suddenly.
no one's talking about Barry.

660
00:30:29.664 --> 00:30:31.666
What if Brit was dating Paxton.

661
00:30:31.800 --> 00:30:33.867
but also had
a secret relationship
with Barry?

662
00:30:34.803 --> 00:30:37.605
Paxton found out.
led to Barry's death by hazing.

663
00:30:38.172 --> 00:30:39.840
The guilt got to be too much.

664
00:30:39.973 --> 00:30:41.075
She finally snapped.

665
00:30:41.208 --> 00:30:42.976
Secrets will do that to you.

666
00:30:43.844 --> 00:30:45.846
Now she's exacting revenge.

667
00:30:45.979 --> 00:30:47.448
Anyone involved
could be in danger.

668
00:30:47.582 --> 00:30:49.316
If Paxton and Sharkey
were there that night.

669
00:30:49.450 --> 00:30:50.552
then so were Badger and Sean.

670
00:30:50.685 --> 00:30:51.919
Those four were inseparable.

671
00:30:52.052 --> 00:30:55.557
Go. Get Sean. Chancellor Bixby
and this Wolverine.

672
00:30:55.690 --> 00:30:57.057
-Badger.
-Whatever.

673
00:30:57.191 --> 00:30:58.793
Put them in protective custody.

674
00:30:58.926 --> 00:31:02.029
And we'll deal with
whatever they did to Barry
once this is done.

675
00:31:02.162 --> 00:31:05.299
And find Brit
before she kills somebody else.

676
00:31:08.435 --> 00:31:11.271
[chattering]

677
00:31:15.810 --> 00:31:17.177
-Oh. hey. Toothbrush.
-Hey.

678
00:31:17.311 --> 00:31:18.747
[Franklin] Where's Sean
and Badger?

679
00:31:19.514 --> 00:31:21.816
I haven't seen 'em.
but they're probably
at the quad.

680
00:31:21.949 --> 00:31:24.151
There's a memorial
for Paxton and Sharkey.

681
00:31:24.284 --> 00:31:25.553
All the houses are going.

682
00:31:25.687 --> 00:31:27.689
Why do you still
have the toothbrush?
It's disgusting.

683
00:31:28.656 --> 00:31:29.858
Commitment.

684
00:31:30.825 --> 00:31:33.227
Okay. Uh. let's split up.

685
00:31:33.360 --> 00:31:35.896
I'll go to the quad.
you sweep the house.
make sure they're not there.

686
00:31:36.029 --> 00:31:37.866
No. I'll go to the quad.
I'm taller.

687
00:31:37.998 --> 00:31:41.435
Hopefully. I can spot
these two in a sea
of Zack. Jakes and Joshs.

688
00:31:41.569 --> 00:31:43.705
-[chuckles] All right.
sounds good.
-All right.

689
00:31:43.838 --> 00:31:47.141
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

690
00:31:51.646 --> 00:31:53.080
[chattering]

691
00:31:53.213 --> 00:31:54.516
Hey. Georgia.

692
00:31:54.649 --> 00:31:56.751
Georgia.
we're looking for Brit.
Have you seen her?

693
00:31:56.885 --> 00:31:59.621
Like an hour ago.
She was headed
towards the woods.

694
00:31:59.754 --> 00:32:01.155
The same woods
where Barry was found?

695
00:32:01.288 --> 00:32:03.792
-I think so.
-Hopefully we're not too late.

696
00:32:11.833 --> 00:32:14.602
[♪ tense music playing]

697
00:32:20.374 --> 00:32:23.377
APD. Anybody here?

698
00:32:26.079 --> 00:32:27.247
Sean?

699
00:32:29.617 --> 00:32:30.752
Badger?

700
00:32:31.985 --> 00:32:33.487
-[indistinct radio chatter]
-[agent 1] Clear!

701
00:32:33.621 --> 00:32:35.489
[agent 2] Let's get a light
on this tree line!

702
00:32:36.089 --> 00:32:37.157
Brit!

703
00:32:37.792 --> 00:32:41.395
It's GBI
Special Agent Mitchell.
We know you're out here.

704
00:32:41.529 --> 00:32:42.831
Badger!

705
00:32:49.671 --> 00:32:52.740
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

706
00:33:20.702 --> 00:33:22.402
[groans] Baby girl.

707
00:33:23.003 --> 00:33:24.204
[exhales]

708
00:33:24.338 --> 00:33:27.107
Somehow. your momma is
still not used to this belly.

709
00:33:27.241 --> 00:33:30.879
even though it feels like
I've been pregnant with you
for a year.

710
00:33:41.455 --> 00:33:42.624
[Franklin] Brit.

711
00:33:42.757 --> 00:33:43.892
[agents speaking indistinctly]

712
00:33:44.024 --> 00:33:45.058
Badger.

713
00:33:45.192 --> 00:33:46.393
[muffled moaning]

714
00:33:48.495 --> 00:33:50.264
-[Faith] Brit!
-[leaves rustling]

715
00:33:50.397 --> 00:33:51.533
[Michael] Sean!

716
00:33:53.400 --> 00:33:54.802
[moaning continues]

717
00:33:55.770 --> 00:33:57.906
[Franklin] Ormewood! Mitchell!

718
00:33:59.172 --> 00:34:01.208
-Come over here!
-[leaves rustling]

719
00:34:01.341 --> 00:34:03.745
[moaning]

720
00:34:04.812 --> 00:34:06.014
She's alive.

721
00:34:06.146 --> 00:34:07.347
[Brit breathing heavily]

722
00:34:10.050 --> 00:34:11.184
[Angie chuckles]

723
00:34:16.356 --> 00:34:17.959
Is that Barry?

724
00:34:20.093 --> 00:34:21.128
[gasps]

725
00:34:24.566 --> 00:34:25.967
[sighs] Sean.

726
00:34:26.601 --> 00:34:29.971
Oh. God. Sean.

727
00:34:31.940 --> 00:34:33.875
-[thud. glass shatters]
-[person groans]

728
00:34:37.712 --> 00:34:39.446
This is Detective Polaski.

729
00:34:40.080 --> 00:34:42.550
I'm at
the Delta Kappa Chi House
on the GAU campus.

730
00:34:42.684 --> 00:34:44.384
